The paper deals with the use of smartphones to monitor human behavior related to psychological state and stress. This falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves the use of statistical models to classify stress levels, which could fall under the categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of smartphones and wearable devices also involves aspects of Cybersecurity (cs.CR) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the health and well-being of the workforce, which could fall under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Other (cs.OH).
